- \( \vec{A}(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{\mu qc \vec{v}}{4\pi (d c + \vec{d} \cdot \vec{v})} \)

Option C:
- \( V(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{q}{4\pi\epsilon_o r} \)
- \( \vec{A}(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{\vec{v}}{c^2} V(\vec{r}, t) \)

Option D:
- \( V(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{q}{4\pi\epsilon_o r} \)
- \( \vec{A}(\vec{r}, t) = \frac{\vec{v}^2}{c^2} V(\vec{r}, t) \)

